    "body": "Hi Guys,\r\nI was experiencing the exact same problem, this is what I found:\r\n\r\n1. Transactions are \"tied\" to the contract deployed code.\r\n2. If I deploy a version of the smart contract, perform a transaction and debug it, it works OK\r\n3. If change the smart contract code, build, deploy and try to debug the same transaction, it FAILS.\r\n4. In order to be able to debug my new code changes, I have to execute a new transaction that will be impacted by the new deployed code. If I try to debug this new transaction, it works OK.\r\n\r\nMy environment:\r\nOS Win10\r\nganache UI\r\ntruffle v5.4.17\r\nnode v16.13.0\r\nnpm v8.1.0\r\n\r\nHope it helps,\r\nG    ",
